<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY:
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC) is proposing to amend its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulations to require power reactor licensees to: Assure that uncontrolled changes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in reactivity, reactor coolant inventory, and loss of subcooled state in the reactor coolant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
system when subcooled conditions are normally being maintained, will not occur when 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the plant is in either a shutdown or low power condition; assure that containment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
integrity is maintained or can be reestablished in a timely manner as needed to prevent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
releases in excess of the current limits in the regulations when the plant is in either a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shutdown or low power condition; establish controls in technical specifications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limiting conditions for operation and surveillance requirements or plant procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required by technical specifications administrative controls for equipment which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
licensee identifies as necessary to perform their safety function when the plant is in a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shutdown or low power condition; evaluate realistically the effect of fires stemming 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
from activities conducted during cold shutdown or refueling conditions, determine 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether such fires could realistically prevent accomplishment of the normal decay heat 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
removal capability, and if so, either provide measures to prevent loss of normal decay 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
heat removal or establish a contingency plan that would ensure that an alternate decay 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
heat removal capability exists; and for licensees of PWRs only, provide 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
instrumentation for monitoring water level in the RCS during midloop operation. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed amendments would provide substantial additional protection to public health 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and safety from the risk of a core-melt accident.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

