<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
For purposes of this appendix A, netting refers to the offsetting of positive and negative mark-to-market values
when determining a current exposure to be used in the calculation of a credit equivalent amount. Any legally enforceable
form of bilateral netting (that is, netting with a single counterparty) of derivative contracts is recognized for
purposes of calculating the credit equivalent amount provided that: 
