<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
Cost Impact 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The FAA estimates that 150 airplanes of U.S. registry would be affected by this proposed AD. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed side-loads test of the engine throttle quadrant would take approximately 17 work hours per airplane
to accomplish the proposed actions, and that the average labor rate is $55 per work hour. Based on these figures, the
total cost impact of this proposed requirement on U.S. operators is estimated to be $140,250, or $935 per airplane.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed abrupt-movement check of the idle stop function of the throttle quadrant would take approximately 1
work hour per airplane to accomplish, at an average labor rate of $55 per work hour. Based on these figures, the total
cost impact of the proposed functional check on U.S. operators is estimated to be $8,250, or $55 per airplane. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed installation of a modified throttle quadrant would take approximately 10 work hours per airplane to
accomplish, at an average labor rate of $55 per work hour. Required parts would be provided by the manufacturer at no
cost to operators. Based on these figures, the total cost impact of the proposed installation on U.S. operators is
estimated to be $82,500, or $550 per airplane. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Based on the figures discussed above, the total cost impact of this proposed AD on U.S. operators is estimated to be
$231,000, or $1,540 per airplane. This total cost impact figure is based on assumptions that no operator has yet accomplished
any of the proposed requirements of this AD action, and that no operator would accomplish those actions in the future
if this AD were not adopted. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
