Securities Act Release No. 5362 (Feb. 2, 1973) (``[t]he Commission has never required a company to publicly disclose
its projections and does not intend to do so now''). The Commission stated that its decision not to mandate disclosure
of forward-looking statements was based on its desire not to deviate too far from its historical position of prohibiting
such disclosure. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=28 g=1 f=3 -->
