<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Another concern voiced by companies is whether to make forward-looking disclosures to securities analysts and institutional
investors, whether in the context of initial public offering ``roadshows'' or otherwise, and the corresponding
liability for any forward-looking statements included in the analysts' reports or statements. Companies complain
that a better balance must be struck between the incentives and disincentives of disclosure to analysts.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
76
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The New York Stock Exchange, the American Stock Exchange, and the National Association of Securities Dealers encourage
listed or quoted corporations to seek out formal and informal contact with analysts to facilitate the accurate pricing
of their securities.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
77
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The Commission also encourages such communications as a complement to disclosure under the Exchange Act.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
