be elicited about the efficacy and potential effects of different safe harbor approaches, the costs and benefits
of each approach, the design of any safe harbor and issues that may be raised by the comment letters. After these hearings,
the Commission will determine whether to propose amendments to the rules regarding forward-looking information.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The hearings will begin at 10 a.m. on February 13, 1995 at 450 Fifth Street, NW., Washington, DC 20549 room 1C30. The
agenda and format for the hearings, as well as the schedule of witnesses will be announced in a subsequent release to
be issued shortly before the hearings commence. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Members of the public interested in testifying at the hearing should notify the Commission in writing of their intention
to appear no later than December 31, 1994. The written notification should include a brief summary of the individual's
intended testimony. Any person who does not wish to appear at the hearing may submit written testimony to be included
in the hearing record. Such written testimony should be received by the Commission no later than January 11, 1995.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
All written notifications, testimony and comment letters should be addressed in triplicate to Jonathan Katz, 450
