Background 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Effective January 1, 1994, the 1993 Act amends section 4081 to impose the diesel fuel tax in the same manner as the gasoline
tax. Thus, tax is imposed on (1) the removal of gasoline and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
diesel fuel (collectively taxable fuel) from any refinery, (2) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the removal of taxable fuel from any terminal, (3) the entry of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
taxable fuel into the United States for consumption, use, or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
warehousing, and (4) the sale of taxable fuel to an unregistered person unless there was a prior taxable removal, entry,
or sale 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the taxable fuel. However, tax does not apply to any entry or removal of taxable fuel transferred in bulk to a refinery
or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
terminal if the persons involved (including the terminal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operator) are registered by the IRS. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

