<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gasoline and alcohol that is 10 percent gasohol, 7.7 percent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gasohol, or 5.7 percent gasohol immediately after the mixture is blended. The determination of whether a particular
mixture is 10 percent gasohol, 7.7 percent gasohol, or 5.7 percent gasohol is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
made on a batch-by-batch basis. A batch of gasohol is a discrete mixture of gasoline and alcohol. If a batch is splash
blended, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the contents of the batch typically correspond to a gasoline 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
meter delivery ticket and an alcohol meter delivery ticket, each of which shows the number of gallons of liquid delivered
into the mixture. In such case, the volume of each component in a batch 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(without adjustment for temperature) ordinarily is determined by the number of metered gallons shown on the delivery
tickets for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the gasoline and alcohol delivered. However, if a blender adds 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
metered gallons of gasoline and alcohol to a tank already 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
containing more than a minor amount of liquid (other than 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gasohol), the determination of whether a batch is gasohol and of its type will be made by taking into account the amount
of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
alcohol and non-alcohol fuel contained in the liquid already in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the tank. Ordinarily, any amount in excess of 0.5 percent of the capacity of the tank will not be considered minor. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
10 percent gasohol
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
_(A) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
In general
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. A batch of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gasoline/alcohol mixture is 10 percent gasohol if it contains at least 10 percent alcohol by volume, without rounding.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Batches containing less than 10 percent but at least 9.8 percent alcohol. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If a batch of mixture contains less than 10 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
percent alcohol but at least 9.8 percent alcohol, without 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rounding, a portion of the batch is considered to be 10 percent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
gasohol. That portion equals the number of gallons of alcohol 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the batch multiplied by 10. Any remaining liquid in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mixture is 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
excess liquid. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If tax was imposed on the excess 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
liquid at the gasohol production rate (as defined in paragraph 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)(1) of this section), the excess liquid in the batch is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
considered to be gasoline with respect to which there is a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
failure to blend into gasohol for purposes of paragraph (g) of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this section. Excess liquid is considered to be removed before 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the removal of the gasohol portion. If tax was imposed on the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
excess liquid at the rate of tax described in section 4081(a), a credit or refund under section 6427(f) is not allowed
with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
respect to the excess liquid. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
7.7 percent gasohol
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
. A batch of gasoline/alcohol 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mixture is 7.7 percent gasohol if and only if it contains at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
least 7.7 percent, but less than 9.8 percent, alcohol by volume, without rounding. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) 
